                        <locus from="1v" to="69v">ff. 1v-69v</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21984">Safar'nāmah</title>
                        <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21984">سفر نامه</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>Brief, yet valuable prose and verse account of the author’s travels across northern India (<placeName>Kashmir</placeName>, <placeName>Punjab</placeName>, <placeName>Haryana</placeName>, and <placeName>Delhi</placeName> states), with interesting details on local epigraphy and descriptions of monuments, gardens, pilgrimage sites, and local history
                           </p>
                           <p>Account additionally contains autobiographical details, descriptions of élite jāgīrs, and the conventions of royal titles
</p>
                           <p>Not dated, but the latest entries and a terminating chronogram state the dates 1851 and 1850, respectively
</p>
                        </note>
                        <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                        <author>
                           <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7431">Munshī Gangā Bishan "Fikrat"</persName>
                           <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7431">منشىٔ گنگا بشن متخلّص به فكرت</persName>
                        </author>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
